Package coffee.khyonieheart.hyacinth.util.marker

package coffee.khyonieheart.hyacinth.util.marker
Collection of documentation annotations that document how a resource may be correctly used. In the future, a utility may be created to scan over a document and ensure that resources with these annotations abide by the contract they say they do.

  • Annotation Interfaces
    Class
    Description
    NoExceptions
    Marker annotation used to declare that a method should not legally throw exceptions or be the cause of any exceptions.
    NotEmpty
    Marker annotation used to declare that a variable-length argument cannot legally contain 0 entries.
    NotNull
    Marker annotation used to declare either that a parameter cannot legally be null, or a method should never return null.
    Nullable
    Marker annotation used to declare that a method may return null, or a parameter can legally be null.
